{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e7d20e19",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Consider an Erdős-Rényi network with N = 3,000 nodes, connected to each other with probability p = 10–3.\n",
    "\n",
    "What is the expected number of links, 〈L〉?\n",
    "In which regime is the network?\n",
    "Calculate the probability pc so that the network is at the critical point\n",
    "Given the linking probability p = 10–3, calculate the number of nodes Ncr so that the network has only one component.\n",
    "For the network in (d), calculate the average degree 〈kcr〉 and the average distance between two randomly chosen nodes 〈d〉.\n",
    "Calculate the degree distribution pk of this network (approximate with a Poisson degree distribution)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "eb3f5aca",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# **Á eftir að klára**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "178b0da3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import networkx as nx\n",
    "import random"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "be051a8b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Expected number os links\n",
    "$$\n",
    "〈L〉 = \\frac{pN (N-1)}{2}\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "139ff394",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Expected number of links: 12497.5\n",
      "avg degree ≈ 5.04\n",
      "largest component size ≈ 4964 (99.28% of nodes)\n",
      "# components = 37\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "N = 5000\n",
    "p = 1e-3  # 10^-3 should be written as 1e-3 for floating point\n",
    "G = nx.erdos_renyi_graph(N, p)\n",
    "\n",
    "L = (p * N * (N - 1)) / 2\n",
    "print(\"Expected number of links:\", L)\n",
    "\n",
    "avg_deg = sum(dict(G.degree()).values())/N\n",
    "largest_cc = max(len(c) for c in nx.connected_components(G))\n",
    "num_cc = nx.number_connected_components(G)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"avg degree ≈ {avg_deg:.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"largest component size ≈ {largest_cc} ({largest_cc/N:.2%} of nodes)\")\n",
    "print(f\"# components = {num_cc}\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
